ays-distinct-element-sum-of-squares-i","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":2913,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["String"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a **0-indexed** binary string `s` having an even length.\n\nA string is **beautiful** if it's possible to partition it into one or more substrings such that:\n\n- Each substring has an **even length**.\n\n- Each substring contains **only** `1`'s or **only** `0`'s.\n\nYou can change any character in `s` to `0` or `1`.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** number of changes required to make the string *`s` *beautiful*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: s = \"1001\"\nOutput: 2\nExplanation: We change s[1] to 1 and s[3] to 0 to get string \"1100\".\nIt can be seen that the string \"1100\" is beautiful because we can partition it into \"11|00\".\nIt can be proven that 2 is the minimum number of changes needed to make the string beautiful.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: s = \"10\"\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: We change s[1] to 1 to get string \"11\".\nIt can be seen that the string \"11\" is beautiful because we can partition it into \"11\".\nIt can be proven that 1 is the minimum number of changes needed to make the string beautiful.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: s = \"0000\"\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: We don't need to make any changes as the string \"0000\" is beautiful already.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= s.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `s` has an even length.\n\n- `s[i]` is either `'0'` or `'1'`.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["String"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a **0-indexed** binary string `s` having an even length.\n\nA string is **beautiful** if it's possible to partition i